result.execSummary:
The defendant Eleanor S. Decorah was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Was originally set for a STC now ready to proceed with a plea and sent hearing.  Defendant pleads Guilty to count 1.  Counts 2 & 3 DRI.

Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  She understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  She understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine (1) contrary to 961.41(3g)(g); Habitual Criminality (1) contrary to 939.62(1)(b).  Counts 2 & 3 DRI.  Defendant exercised her right to allocution.

Joint recommendation sentence withheld, 2yrs probation, any other programing deemed appropriate, AODA, risk & needs, absolute sobriety. 83 days of presentence credit.  Defense agrees with 83 days.

Court adopts joint recommendation orders sentence withheld, 2 years probation, AODA, maintain absolute sobriety, Risk & needs, court costs. no control substances without a prescription.  DNA requirement.  If able to find a in patient treatment- discuss with agent. CC.  83 days of credit if revoked.
